Switch to catboost's libcxxcuda11 fallback when the host clang is <18.

Upstream catboost unconditionally builds against the modern bundled `libcxx`.
Older clang (pre-18) chokes on parts of that vendored libcxx, so catboost
also ships `libcxxcuda11` (its CUDA-compatible libc++ fork) as a fallback.
This patch picks libcxxcuda11 when CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_VERSION < 18, and
keeps the upstream libcxx path for newer clang.

Our recipe pins `clangxx >=18`, so today the `else()` branch is always
taken -- this is defensive in case the pin is ever relaxed.

Applies the same change to all three linux subdirs (x86_64 / aarch64 /
ppc64le); only the file path differs.

--- a/contrib/libs/cxxsupp/CMakeLists.linux-x86_64.txt
+++ b/contrib/libs/cxxsupp/CMakeLists.linux-x86_64.txt
@@ -12,7 +12,12 @@
 # Please refer to the build instructions in the repository for more information about manual
 # changes in this file.

-add_subdirectory(libcxx)
+if (CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_VERSION VERSION_LESS 18)
+    add_subdirectory(libcxxcuda11)
+else ()
+    add_subdirectory(libcxx)
+endif()
+
 add_subdirectory(libcxxabi-parts)
 add_subdirectory(libcxxrt)
 add_subdirectory(builtins)
@@ -22,6 +27,16 @@ add_library(contrib-libs-cxxsupp INTERFACE)

 target_link_libraries(contrib-libs-cxxsupp INTERFACE
   contrib-libs-linux-headers
-  libs-cxxsupp-libcxx
 )

+if (CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_VERSION VERSION_LESS 18)
+    target_link_libraries(contrib-libs-cxxsupp INTERFACE
+      libs-cxxsupp-libcxxcuda11
+    )
+else ()
+    target_link_libraries(contrib-libs-cxxsupp INTERFACE
+      libs-cxxsupp-libcxx
+    )
+endif()
+
+
